description:
Currently search returns all matching results. Users often want to filter by:
- File path patterns (e.g., only search in 'src/', exclude 'tests/')
- Language type (e.g., only TypeScript files)
- Date modified (e.g., recently changed files)

Add optional filter parameters to the search_code tool:
```typescript
interface SearchOptions {
  query: string;
  limit?: number;
  pathPattern?: string;  // glob pattern
  languages?: string[];  // e.g., ['typescript', 'javascript']
  modifiedAfter?: Date;
}
```

The main function doesn't handle SIGTERM/SIGINT for graceful shutdown. This can lead to:
- Incomplete index writes
- Orphaned dashboard server processes
- Corrupted state

Add signal handlers:
```typescript
process.on('SIGTERM', async () => {
  console.error('[lance-context] Shutting down gracefully...');
  await stopDashboard();
  process.exit(0);
});

process.on('SIGINT', async () => {
  console.error('[lance-context] Interrupted, shutting down...');
  await stopDashboard();
  process.exit(0);
});
```
